.SS "\fBsocket_t\fP accepterClt (const \fBsocket_t\fP sockEcoute)"

.PP
Accepts a client connection request\&. Blocks waiting for an incoming connection on the listening socket, then accepts it and returns a new socket for communication with the connected client\&. The client's address information is stored in the returned socket structure\&.
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIsockEcoute\fP Listening socket to receive the connection request 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
Dialogue socket connected by the server with a client
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
This function blocks until a client connection request arrives 
.PP
The returned socket is ready for bidirectional communication 
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBcreerSocketEcoute()\fP 
.RE
.PP

.SS "void adr2struct (struct sockaddr_in * addr, char * adrIP, short port)"

.PP
Converts human-readable address format to BSD socket structure\&. Transforms an IP address string and port number into a sockaddr_in structure suitable for use with Berkeley sockets API\&. Handles address family configuration, byte order conversion, and structure initialization\&.
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIaddr\fP BSD socket addressing structure to fill (INET domain) 
.br
\fIadrIP\fP IP address string of the socket (e\&.g\&., '192\&.168\&.1\&.1' or '0\&.0\&.0\&.0') 
.br
\fIport\fP Port number of the socket
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The domain depends on the chosen mode (TCP/UDP) 
.PP
The addr parameter is modified by this function 
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBcreerSocketAdr()\fP 
.RE
.PP

.SS "\fBsocket_t\fP connecterClt2Srv (char * adrIP, short port)"

.PP
Creates a calling socket and connects to a server\&. Creates a TCP socket and initiates a connection to the server whose address is provided as parameter\&. This function is used by client applications to establish connections to servers\&.
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIadrIP\fP IP address of the server to connect to 
.br
\fIport\fP TCP port of the server to connect to 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
Socket connected to the server provided as parameter
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
Always creates a SOCK_STREAM (TCP) socket 
.PP
This function blocks until connection is established or fails 
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBcreerSocket()\fP 
.RE
.PP

.SS "\fBsocket_t\fP creerSocket (int mode)"

.PP
Creates a socket of type DGRAM or STREAM\&. Creates a socket using the Berkeley sockets API with the specified mode\&. Supports both connection-oriented (SOCK_STREAM/TCP) and connectionless (SOCK_DGRAM/UDP) communication modes\&.
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fImode\fP Connection mode: SOCK_STREAM (connected/TCP) or SOCK_DGRAM (connectionless/UDP) 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
Socket created according to the chosen mode
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
If an invalid mode is provided, defaults to SOCK_STREAM 
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBcreerSocketAdr()\fP 
.RE
.PP

.SS "\fBsocket_t\fP creerSocketAdr (int mode, char * adrIP, short port)"

.PP
Creates a socket of type DGRAM/STREAM with specified addressing\&. Creates a socket with the specified mode and binds it to the provided IP address and port\&. This function combines socket creation and address binding in a single operation\&.
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fImode\fP Connection mode: SOCK_STREAM (TCP) or SOCK_DGRAM (UDP) 
.br
\fIadrIP\fP IP address to bind the socket to 
.br
\fIport\fP Port number to bind the socket to 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
Socket created in the chosen domain with the provided addressing
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBcreerSocket()\fP, \fBadr2struct()\fP 
.RE
.PP

.SS "\fBsocket_t\fP creerSocketEcoute (char * adrIP, short port)"

.PP
Creates a listening socket with the provided addressing\&. Creates a TCP socket, binds it to the specified address and port, and puts it in listening mode to accept incoming client connections\&. This function is specifically designed for server applications\&.
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIadrIP\fP IP address of the server to put in listening mode 
.br
\fIport\fP TCP port of the server to put in listening mode 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
Socket created with the provided addressing and in listening state
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The mode is necessarily SOCK_STREAM (TCP) 
.PP
Listen backlog is configured for pending connections 
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBaccepterClt()\fP 
.RE
.PP

